The evidence with the title 'Fewer voters identify as republicans | Pew Research Center ' says Mar 20, 2008  ... Of the 37 % who claim no party identification, 15% lean Democratic, 10% lean Republican , and 12% have no leaning either way.  ... Currently , 39% of registered voters in the 13 states Kerry won by more than five points identify themselves as Democrats , compared with 21 % who identify as Republicans. 
